African swine fever, Mali
-------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 23 Feb 2016 from Dr Halimatou Kone Traore, [National Director, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Rural Development in charge of Livestock, Fisheries, and Food Safety], Bamako, Mali

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 1 Jan 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 19 Feb 2016
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease in the country
Causal agent: African swine fever [ASF] virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (basic and advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks:
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Sanekuy, Saneykuy, Tominian, Segou
Date of start of the outbreak: 1 Jan 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / 1003 / 130 / 31 / 0 / 16
Affected population: this is the local swine breed, all sex and ages mixed. These are sedentary animals.
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Swine / 12.96 / 3.09 / 23.85 / 4.69
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: introduction of new live animals; illegal movement of animals; contact with infected animal(s) at grazing/watering; swill feeding

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; disinfection/disinfestations; traceability; quarantine; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; zoning; no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Central Veterinary Laboratory (national laboratory) / Swine / real-time PCR / 19 Feb 2016 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

